quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  23,75,"And though We had Mercy on them and removed what distress is on them, still they would stubbornly persist in their transgression, wandering blindly"
  23,76,"Indeed We seized them with punishment, but neither did they humble themselves to their Lord, nor did they invoke with submission to Him"
  23,77,"Until, when We open for them a gate of severe punishment, then lo! They will be plunged into it"
  23,78,"It is He, Who has created for you hearing, sight, and hearts; you give little thanks"
  23,79,"And it is He Who has created you on the earth, and to Him, you shall be gathered back"
  23,80,"And it is He Who gives life and causes death, and in His control is the alternation of night and day. Will you not then understand"
  23,81,But they say just like what their forefathers said
  23,82,"They said: “When we are dead and have become dust and bones, shall we be resurrected indeed"
  23,83,"Surely, we have been promised this, we and our forefathers before us! This is not but the tales of the ancients!”"
  23,84,"Say: “To whom belongs the earth and whatever is in it? If you know!”"
  23,85,"They will say: “(It is) Allah’s!” Say: “Will you not then remember?”"
  23,86,"Say: “Who is the Lord of the 7 heavens and Lord of the Great Throne?”"
  23,87,"They will say: “(It is) for Allah.” Say: “Then will you not fear Allah?”"
  23,88,"Say: “In whose hand is the sovereignty of everything? He protects all, and is there any protector against Him, if you know?”"
  23,89,"They will say: “(It is) for Allah.” Say: “How then are you deceived (from the truth)?”"